This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it focuses on comparing the human visual system with deep neural networks on image classification tasks. Additionally, the use of distorted images and limiting display time to 100ms suggests a focus on early visual processing, which is a common topic in the cs.CV field. 

The paper also touches on neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it compares the performance of the human visual system with state-of-the-art deep neural networks. 

Furthermore, the paper's focus on performance evaluation and comparison suggests a potential fit for the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. 

Finally, the paper's consideration of the limitations of the human visual system and potential implications for future research suggests a potential fit for the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category.
